train_ex4 — Exercise 4 train (numerical integration, MPI)

What it does
- Reads acceleration a(t) from ../functiongen/ex4.h (1 Hz table, linear interp between seconds).
- Integrates with explicit Euler: v += a*dt, x += v*dt; no antiderivatives.
- MPI: splits step indices 0..N-1 across ranks; each rank receives (v,x) from rank-1 and sends to rank+1.

Build (ECC login node or compute node)
  cd train_ex4
  make

Run (examples)
  mpirun -np 1 ./train_ex4 --dt 0.001
  mpirun -np 1 ./train_ex4 --dt 0.0001
  mpirun -np 4 ./train_ex4 --dt 0.0001

Scaling note
- This is a pipeline along time: rank r waits for rank r-1. Wall time is roughly the sum of per-rank work plus communication, so you may not see ideal speedup. For your report, plot measured completion time vs P and explain the loop-carried dependency (see compare.c comments in assignment-4/compare/).

Output fields
- final_position_m vs 122000 m target, final and peak velocity vs 320 km/h limit.
